                },
                {
                    "text": " reached land"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Called 'hurricane' in the Atlantic, 'typhoon' near Asia, and 'cyclone' near India/Australia—but all are the same type of storm."
        },
        {
            "word": "tornado",
            "wordType": "noun",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "A violently spinning column of air that touches the ground, often appearing as a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "funnel-shaped cloud",
                    "highlight": true
